        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The Pradhan Mantri Matsya Sampada Yojana: Inputs for fresh water Aquaculture, including Composite fish culture, Scampi, Pangasius, Tilapia, etc, introduced by the Ministry Of Fisheries, Animal Husbandry &amp; Dairying, Government of India, aims to expand fisheries production in Haryana. This centrally sponsored scheme is jointly funded 50% by the Central Government and 50% by the State Government. It provides input cost subsidies for the first crop in newly constructed ponds under PMMSY, aiming to promote aquaculture in urban and semi-urban areas.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n- The project cost is: 4,00,000/- per hectare\n\n> **Subsidy Distribution:**\n\n\n1. 40% of the project cost for General Category beneficiaries\n1. 60% of the project cost for SC/Women beneficiaries\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme under Pradhan Mantri Matsya Sampada Yojana (PMMSY) provides input cost subsidy for freshwater aquaculture in newly constructed ponds to expand fisheries production in Haryana.",
        "exclusions_md": "<br>\n\n",
